In [3]:
x = df.Month
y1 = df['Total Construction']
y2 = df['Private Construction']
y3 = df['Public Construction']

# Create graph and assign Figure and Axes objects to variables fig and ax
fig, ax = plt.subplots()

# Plot the data and set other Axes attributes
ax.plot(x,y1,label='Total Construction')                                  # Add y1 data to graph and create label for the legend
ax.plot(x,y2,label='Private Construction')
ax.plot(x,y3,label='Public Construction')   # Add y2 data to graph and create label for the legend
ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)                                                 # Remove right spine
ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)    # Remove top spine
ax.legend(loc = 'best', prop = {'size':'medium'})   # Add legend and format it
ax.set_xlim(0,x.max()+1)                                                              # Set min and max for y axis
ax.set_ylim(0,1.1*y1.max())                                                           # Set min and max for y axis

# Set x-axis attributes
ax.xaxis.set_label_text('Month',fontsize = 12)
ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(which = 'both', top = False, bottom = True, labelbottom = True)  # Turn tick marks off for top x axis

# Set y-axis attributes: the parameter 'both' refers to both major and minor tick marks
ax.yaxis.set_label_text('Construction Spending',fontsize = 12)      # Title for the vertical axis
ax.yaxis.set_tick_params(which = 'both', right = False, left = True, labelleft = True)   # Turn tick marks off for right y axis

# Set Figure attributes
fig.set_size_inches(7,5)             # Set size of figure
fig.suptitle('Construction Spending in the US 2002-13',fontsize='x-large')
plt.savefig('first.jpg')

In [8]:
def create_regress_col(row, intercept, slope):
    return float(intercept) + float(row[0]) * slope
    
df['regress'] = df.apply(create_regress_col,args = (intercept,slope),axis = "columns")
df.style.format({
    'Private Construction': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'regress': '{:,.0f}'.format
})

In [11]:
dfQtr = pd.DataFrame()
cycleLen = 12
for i in range(int(len(df.index)/cycleLen)):
    newData = pd.DataFrame({i:df['R1'].iloc[i*cycleLen:(i+1)*cycleLen]})
    newData.index = range(0,len(newData))
    dfQtr = pd.concat([dfQtr,newData],axis=1)

fig,ax = plt.subplots()
ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)                                                 # Remove right spine
ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
fig.set_size_inches(7,5)             # Set size of figure
fig.suptitle('Private Construction Periodicity',fontsize='large')
plt.xlabel('Month') 
ax.plot(dfQtr)

In [13]:
avg = []
for i in range(len(dfQtr.index)):
    avg.append(dfQtr.iloc[i].mean())

dfQtr = pd.concat([dfQtr,pd.DataFrame({'avg':avg})], axis=1)

fig,ax = plt.subplots()
c = 180
ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)                                                 # Remove right spine
ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
fig.set_size_inches(7,5)             # Set size of figure
fig.suptitle('Private Construction Periodicity with Average',fontsize='large')
red_patch = mpatches.Patch(color='red', label='Average')
plt.legend(handles=[red_patch])
for col in dfQtr.columns.values:
    if col == 'avg':
        ax.plot(dfQtr[col], c = 'r')
    else:
        ax.plot(dfQtr[col], c = 'k')
plt.xlabel('Month')         
plt.savefig('third.jpg')
In [14]:
df['S'] = np.NaN
df['error'] = np.NaN
df['R2'] = np.NaN
df['Forecast'] = np.NaN
S = dfQtr['avg'].tolist()

for i in df.index:
    df.loc[i,'S'] = S[i%cycleLen]
    df.loc[i,'R2'] = df.loc[i,'R1'] - df.loc[i,'S']
    df.loc[i,'Forecast'] = df.loc[i,'regress'] + df.loc[i,'S']
    df.loc[i,'error'] = df.loc[i,'R2'] / df.loc[i,'Private Construction']
df.style.format({
    'Private Construction': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'regress': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'R1': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'S': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'R2': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'Forecast':'{:,.0f}'.format,
    'error': '{:.4f}'.format
})

def create_regress_col(row, intercept, slope):
    return float(intercept) + float(row[0]) * slope
    
df['regress'] = df.apply(create_regress_col,args = (intercept,slope),axis = "columns")
df.style.format({
    'Public Construction': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'regress': '{:,.0f}'.format
})

dfQtr = pd.DataFrame()
cycleLen = 12
for i in range(int(len(df.index)/cycleLen)):
    newData = pd.DataFrame({i:df['R1'].iloc[i*cycleLen:(i+1)*cycleLen]})
    newData.index = range(0,len(newData))
    dfQtr = pd.concat([dfQtr,newData],axis=1)

fig,ax = plt.subplots()
ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)                                                 # Remove right spine
ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
fig.set_size_inches(7,5)             # Set size of figure
fig.suptitle('Public Construction Periodicity',fontsize='large')
ax.plot(dfQtr)

df['error'] = np.NaN
df['R2'] = np.NaN
df['Forecast'] = np.NaN
S = dfQtr['avg'].tolist()
for i in df.index:
    df.loc[i,'S'] = S[i%cycleLen]
    df.loc[i,'R2'] = df.loc[i,'R1'] - df.loc[i,'S']
    df.loc[i,'Forecast'] = df.loc[i,'regress'] + df.loc[i,'S']
    df.loc[i,'error'] = df.loc[i,'R2'] / df.loc[i,'Public Construction']
df.style.format({
    'Public Construction': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'regress': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'R1': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'S': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'R2': '{:,.0f}'.format,
    'Forecast':'{:,.0f}'.format,
    'error': '{:.4f}'.format
})
